reviews.text: Very impressed with all the Organic selections here and the knowledge of most if not all of the folks working here! I will Definitely be coming back as often as I'm here in the area and Highly recommend shopping here if you buy healthy foods and drinks! I was also Very impressed with the Kombucha on tap and all the flavors, WOW, Fantastic! 😁👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼

Home to hard to find Vegan specials in the Albany, New York metro area. My Bacon is manufactured in Green Island, New York and is sold at Honest Weight Food Co-op. Which also has several vegan cheeses and frozen vegan products. I have been a customer since the early 2000's and shop there at least twice a week. Still not a member yet. But this is one of the places I frequent to purchase my groceries. The staff are very friendly and informative on the products sold. I must add they care about the freshness of what they carry and serve.
Was there on January 31, 2024 to purchase some items for my Wife, ( SHE LOVES THE HUMMUS WRAPS AND SEVERAL OTHER ITEMS, I cannot come home empty handed 🤣 ) there were a few items that were on the shelf with an expiration date of today January 31, 2024, I asked the staff in the deli if I can ask for a fresher one to be made and the gentleman in the deli made a few new ones, so I ended up purchasing 2 Hummus wraps, which I will say are very delicious 👍. I enjoy shopping at Honest Weight because of the VERY POSITIVE CUSTOMER SERVICE INTERACTION 👍👍👍👍👍

The freshest, best tasting packaged meat and chicken at any store in the area. Love the Field Day line for organic items. Love the specialty/international section. Also love the monthly contributions to different charities. Agree with some other reviewers that some of the volunteers/staff working there can be unnecessarily patronizing and unfriendly. However, most volunteers/staff there are very helpful and friendly. It would be helpful to allow a higher number of items through self check out, especially if it’s not busy. I prefer self check out and find myself limiting what I buy so I can go through that line. Thanks for providing our community with clean food!

I’m always in a great mood. Always!!
I enjoy the produce sold at honest weight but for some reason this Very rude older woman seemed to get under my skin as opposed to the lady who greeted me at customer service.
I get it, not everyone is a morning person. Maybe they can schedule her later in the day after she stables her attitude
I will make it my business to use self service for now on and never have a conversation with any employee. I feel the culture should be more pleasant and comfortable and compassionate with all worker And customers alike
It’s not that serious you’re a cashier and my effort to spread joy will be limited. Thanks see you next visit 🤔
Great co-op. Bulk section is my favorite. Coffee selections are top notch. Fish and meat you can trust. Plants and seeds for your garden. A very pleasant, calm experience every time I visit!

reviews.text:
Reasonably priced, super friendly service and great menu! I wish I found this place sooner. A great option for lunch near me. Salads, sandwiches, burgers, breakfast options, and cold brew.

Plus you can see the whole grill and it is exceptionally clean, the food is made to order.
Local small deli shop, good sandwiches, at reasonable prices. good food, but not really a coffee shop unless you want regular hot black coffee kind of deal

The staff here are all incredibly friendly and the owner is a really sweet lady who always stops to say hello.  I come here whenever I am in Albany.  The crispy chicken wrap is my favorite, and the onion rings are delicious too. If you're not a fan of crowds, come around 2:30 because it's nearly empty at that time, but it's packed earlier in the lunch hour.
The food is delicious. The staff were polite and attentive. I look forward to visiting again.

Great friendly people and great food
Prices changes but good food

reviews.text:
A must visit place for those seeking knowledge! There is nothing like a real book in your hands to read. This experience can't be beat and you can feel it when you walk inside this bookstore.
We picked up Napoleon Hill's "Law of Success", and there are so many other great books and other stuff from 'games', 'movies' like Harry Potter merchandise, and so many board games..
Walk in and be transfixed.
The payment counter staff are friendly and smiling.

I honestly love the Barnes and Nobles. They get five stars from me. I’ve been coming here since I moved here over a decade ago.

I love to read and I appreciate that they are still around and make physical books.

The staff is pretty nice. I haven’t had any negative interactions with any staff.

The store is clean, updated with new books and stuff.

My review is more for the Starbucks within the BN.

I love their snack selection. I really wish more Starbucks carried options like these. My dilemma is that they don’t restock the items and that’s saddening- which is why I rate them 3 stars. I’m not sure if that’s an organizational decision or location decision but it’s midkey frustrating. I love pastries, so far this place had fairly decent sized and tasty options.

Anywho, the staff is awesome they are always kind and helpful. They move relatively quickly for the amount of people that come in the store.

I would definitely recommend stopping in and bringing the kiddies too. They have a beautiful kid section for books in the Barnes and Nobles. I’ll be sure to update pictures soon.

Barnes and Noble never disappoints! Books, games, puzzles, music, movies - all sorts of media to browse and buy! This location has in-store restrooms, and a Starbucks for some yummy snacks and a coffee - there is also a little cafe area there to sit and read while you enjoy your food. The children's play area is spacious and has a great array of books for baby through early elementary. Shelving nearby has kids books and parenting style books. This location can be entered via the mall or its own entrance from outside.

Worst customer service I have ever experienced. The manager Refused to open gate to mall for 7 month pregnant woman who was parked on other side of the mall with no announcements or warnings of closing the back gate. It was just 2 minutes past six o’clock. And not only was our sale refused when the store was open but there was no warning when we walked in through the mall entrance just before 6pm that they would be closing the mall entrance to the store. Absolutely unacceptable. There was also an elderly man as well as another lady who heard no announcements yet were forced to walk around the front of the building in 92 degree weather to get back into the mall to get to where they parked. Utterly disgusting.
Haven't been here in awhile but it's still a great place to come and relax 😁

reviews.text: The employees here can't be bothered to put aside a personal conversation to pay attention to the customers they are cashing out. It's a gas station, I'm not expecting top tier customer service but it's a pretty bad experience to not even be acknowledged by the cashier. At least a kiosk says thank you.

Their card/app is awesome, it says I saved $100 over the years. There is always a free drink or coffee too on the app. It is rare for a business to give away stuff for free, but they seem to be prospering from their generosity. Their coffee is great too and the store is amazing.

Cumberland Farms is one of the greatest places for when I’m on the road. I always look forward to a decent meatball sub and they’re wide selection of drinks. The night crew seems relatively new, but they had no problem heating up my meatball sub and directing me to the marinara sauce, which is next to a whole plethora of condiments
Always been fantastic. I love walking into a store where every worker smiles!
Cashier was very helpful and friendly. I will be returning 🌸

reviews.text:
I go to Starbucks every morning as I’m sure many people do. I have had to go out of my way to go to this store because the other Starbucks on my route to work is never in stock and generally I cannot order ahead.
This morning I preordered a venti (very basic) drink and egg bites about 15 minutes before I would be reaching the store. My drink was done but not the egg bites. After waiting about 15 minutes my food was still not ready and the employees did not seem to have any care. I ended up walking out without my food so I would not be late for work. The food is made in a microwave people…

Love the food they have at Starbucks, and the lattes are decent 🤷‍♂️
This Starbucks was the same consistent quality. Good job guys! 👍😅

I rarely go to starbucks because dunkin is cheaper, you get more for your money. My fiance and i decided to splurge and get drinks and 2 sausage bacon and egg wraps. The frappuccino i got had tons of whipped cream in the bottom and top so i got virtually no drink. The wraps were comprised of egg and potato with a single half piece of bacon and 1 small nickel sized bite of sausage at the bottom of the wrap(this was the case for both wraps). My fiances grande pink drink was absolutely full of ice with probably a 1/2 cup of actual drink. So disappointing.. we are charged so much for these items but we really dont get what we pay for.

Coffee was good.
Staff was kind and prompt with order taking.
Drive thru

Today, I visited my lovely place, Starbucks. One of the staff members took my order through the drive-thru. He was a really nice person. I not only received my coffee but also a smile on my face. I really forgot about my problems. I truly appreciate his gentless, politeness, and for making my day brighter.

reviews.text: Never a bad experience here! The attentive and friendly service from the bartenders, especially Sarah R., Drew, and Dave are unmatched. Very considerate and top tier energy, one of my favorite places to eat and have amazing drinks just because of them .

Food was great. Really delicious Breakfast and servings and all. Great ambience. The only problem is that , our total was $46.11 for two people, One coffee, two french toast breakfast. I got $20 bill from my friend and i gave the server a $20 bill and my card to split up. The server just left and helped himself to $20 and charged my card $46.11. we were confused as to why would the server just helped himself to $20 tip. i was not going to tip him almost 50% of my bill. the customer service was average.

They are just an upscale breakfast place with New York City vibes. I went back after a day and talked to the manager lady. She almost yelled at me, for not making it clear then. Whatever lady I was with a friend trying to have a good brunch, didnt feel like doing the math then and there.

Very busy on a Sunday morning. Wait for a table was only 15 minutes, or there was room at the bar to split right away. We sat at the bar and were greeted right away by our server. Put in our coffee order, and we also put an order in for the French toast sticks. We got our French toast sticks in about 10 minutes. Right as we finished them up, our breakfast came out. The timing was perfect. French toast sticks were excellent, and you could easily make a meal out of them. We ordered the Nashville hot buritto with home fries. Order of eggs with toast and hash and also home fries. All the food was hot when it came out. The buritto had a nice amount of chicken inside of it. This is a place we will go back to and would be worth waiting to get a table.

Very cozy and welcoming dining room. Nice bar with TV's. Very friendly and attentive staff. We had breakfast and it was delicious. Nice seasonal specials as and regular comfort favorites. Nice seasonal cocktails as well. Lots of brunch and lunch offerings as well.

Cafe Madison re design. Looks delicious. Tasted great. Kind of slow. No fault of servers.

Great breakfast place and a staple of the neighborhood.

I'm so upset this morning I decided to get breakfast for my co workers and walked in the staff was amazing and friendly I got a sandwich and bagels for my co workers and as I'm eating my sandwich I see pure green/blue in my sandwich i open it up and the egg is completely covered in mold! Update i have reached out and no one has gotten back to me. Hence the review

This is my go-to chain for a delicious BLT on their amazing Parmesan bagel. I absolutely love it! This particular location has the added convenience of a drive-through, which is a big plus. Like all its locations the coffee is horrible. I do wish they had some seating available, as it's always nice to have the option to sit and enjoy your meal. Despite that, the quality of the food and the drive-through convenience keep me coming back. Highly recommend!

In my opinion,  the best Bagels in the capital district.  They boil them.  You can taste the difference.  They also offer a few gormet flavors, for slightly more money.  The standard flavors are still my favorite!
I go here to treat my guests and my employer buys them for us. My wife absolutely adores their quality. They’re just a cut above the competition. Prices are market.

Bruggers Are The Best Bagels Around! Wide selection. Nice bagel sandwiches. Select toppings. I like to relax by the window and read. It would be nice if they had space for someone to play live acoustic music. It would be nice ambiance.

reviews.text:
Great little Mexican restaurant in a chill part of Albany. Cocktails were good and the food was definitely on-point. The restaurant isn't that large, so I would highly recommend reservations.

If you're in town and have a craving for Mexican, try this place out.
Really tasty food and very friendly staff. Chef must be the best in town. Highly recommended when you are in Albany. Great prices as well.

The best Mexican food I have ever eaten! Great Margaritas which were authentic and strong, not a huge goblet of sweet and sour mix. The Tamales were our favourite, delicious flavour and texture and great side dishes. Big portions, amazing staff, reasonable price and great flavour!

Quant little store front restaurant. While small the space doesn’t feel cramped, food was delicious- steak fajitas were on point. Service and general atmosphere were good. I think it’s as close to Mexican as you’ll find.

Worth the stop inside

Amazing place with nice decor and very friendly staff. The food is good and the price is reasonable. We ordered the nachos which was huge and two of us couldn’t finish it. The tacos were good as well.

I can never say enough good things about uncommon grounds, everyone who works there is great and the food is always fantastic.

Writing this review I'm tempted to go eat there now. Were they open at least.

Edit, ate there again today. A perfect healthy harvest bagel always hits the spot!!

When a small business knows how to do it, they thrive. Every uncommon grounds is always warm with customers. Great coffee, always a free trade option. Also, In my experience, the order process is smooth, start to finish. I'd always recommend this place, great since the 1990s.

Visited here around 11am on a Saturday and the line was to the door (not a bad sign). The line moved fairly quickly. Quite a variety of bagels, cream cheese, sandwiches, coffees, etc. I ordered the Lox of love (I believe that was the name) on a pumpernickel bagel along with a Dirty chai (I forgot what they call it there) made with oat milk. It was very good. Couldn’t finish the entire bagel so I ate half and saved the other half. There were a couple seats available but I took mine to go. Staff was friendly and helpful. Will definitely go again!

reviews.text: I’ve had 2 or 3 occasions where I get to the drive through and I hear nothing for over 5 minutes. And when they do, it takes even more time to get the food. And these times have been around evening when there were barely any cars. I’m only rating 1/5 for service. Food is typical quality which isn’t bad of course. And if you leave from the line without giving your code, no refund. Great stuff…

Don't go here they are just a scam. I put in a mobile order and after arriving to pick it up all the doors were locked. One of the managers told me the dinning room was closed but they would go check on my order. After waiting for 20-25 minutes my order my order was marked as picked up and I never received it. I tried calling the restaurant to inquire about it but no one answered the phone. So if you want to go someplace and have your money stolen and not get any food this is the place for you!

My family and I are leaving from visiting for the weekend. The man that greeted us in the drive thru (didn’t get his name, but 5/12 at 11:50am) was very friendly and enthusiastic. Food was great! The workers took their time to ensure we had everything that we ordered.

I’ve never experienced a McDonald’s location worse than this one… trash all over floors very unsanitary bunch of hang out inside location workers just lounging around goofing off with the there friends (customers) I really don’t understand how this place is still standing at this point. Literally trashed… no one wearing gloves or hair nets I mean really I’ve never seen such a horrible location they really need to rethink the staff they have hired. reviews.text: I don’t know why this place doesn’t have higher stars. It’s such a cute cafe! Tons of options and seating. Lots of baked goods and coffee/tea options too. Our server was so sweet and accommodating. The special was a blueberry French toast and it was amazing. The cream cheese stuffed French toast with strawberries was also soo good. They have breakfast and lunch served all day which is awesome. Definitely going to go back. Decent prices too.

Great breakfast and lunch place. Eaten here many times. Friendly service. Fresh food.

We kinda had brunch. Eggs Benedict , a Breakfast Quesadilla, Waffles w bacon inside and eggs, and a Chicken wrap. All excellent.

Came here for brunch on a weekday around 10a. Plenty of lot parking in Stuyvesant Plaza. Seated immediately. Good coffee. Ordered dessert first. The coconut cloud cake lived up to its name, very light, not too sweet, with a whipped frosting. I had Texas eggs (migas essentially) in a skillet. Had crispy hash browns, eggs, cheese, tortilla chips, salsa, black beans mixed together. It hit the spot. My companion also loved his cake and the cheese fries (with bacon) but was less enthused about the falafel wrap. About $70 for the meal. Excellent, friendly service.

Pretty big menu with lots of coffee and drink specials.  We went for breakfast and the old school, small diner feel was welcoming.   Waitress was great and the food was very good.  Better than fast casual and quicker and cheaper than a fancier restaurant .

We came for lunch, and the place was packed with 20-30mins wait. The food was great. The omelet and the potato that i got were cooked well, and they're a bit hard. My kids got some sandwiches, and theirs was good. The grilled cheese sandwich was ok "not in the photos". My wife got the salad, and she loved it.

reviews.text: i never order here anymore because they continuously make my order incorrectly. last time i ordered here i got an iced drink and it was warm with no ice. at least this time it had a few ice cubes (i got light ice this time) but they put whip when i asked for none. will definitely be walking into the target starbucks rather than coming to this one again.

As soon as I walked in, all of the staff was busy, so I wasn't acknowledged right away. I noticed that this happens often at Starbucks. I still think that an acknowledgment is needed to ensure that someone knows that you are there. However, the associate who took care of me was great. The tables were a bit dirty. The music was fun to listen to, but it was a bit too high. If I were there with someone to talk to, I would not last long because of the music being too loud. Overall, this Starbucks is great.

I was just at the Starbucks, I go here often, and my drinks either take a really long time or are messed up.

I went to the Starbucks today and send my fiancé in to pick up my two drinks,. The woman at the counter, stated that there was only one drink in the order and didn’t believe my fiancé when he said that there were two drinks - even though on the cup the sticker said “1 of 2 drinks.” My fiancé then came out to grab my phone so he could show the lady that there were in fact, two drinks in the order. When she saw the drink that I had ordered (lavender oatmilk latte with 1 espresso) , she asked my fiancé. “Okay how do you make that to which she responded “Oh I have no idea.” I had ordered one espresso because I’m breast-feeding, and cannot have over a certain amount of caffeine a day. When the drink finally came out 20 minutes later, it tasted like dirt. It must have been either four+ espresso, or cold brew coffee? It tasted bitter and old. The lavender was not mixed into the drink at all, absolutely disgusting.

I NEVER give anyone 1 star. This place is getting one star. Service is trash. They don't even say a word when your order is ready when you're sitting there waiting for 15 minutes for 2 drinks. This is the only Starbucks where I've seen the staff look stupid and no idea how to do their job. Playing on their phones. Any other star bucks I've been to has been amazing. Let me know my drinks were ready too. Here they made me feel totally forgotten. Anyone could have taken my drinks as they were sitting on the counter, hidden from where I was sitting. I shouldn't have to sit for 15 minutes not knowing anything. Just shout the order out when it's done if needed. The one in target is better
This is one if the nicest Starbucks ever. The staff is always so helpful and goes above n beyond for costumer service

reviews.text: Staff was friendly, helpful and professional!  The ambiance was relaxing and very interesting given the history of the building. The food arrived fresh and was served by someone who seemed proud and happy to present the fare. Drinks were delicious, food amount was ample and flavorful and we didn’t feel rushed or pressured to end our experience. Highly recommend.

The food was absolutely awesome and them having a beer license was very nice as well for brunch. The servers were polite and I had no complaints. For those who care the atmosphere is on the fruity side. Other then that if I were in Albany again, definitely will be making a return.

What a wonderful discovery downtown Albany tucked away in a remodeled colonial home.

It's a great place for brunch, and I highly recommend the pancakes if for nothing else than the locally sourced organic syrup. Awesome.

Hot chocolate, if you're a fan, will not disappoint. Coffee was great too.

If you're in Albany and you're hungry on the weekend, definitely add this to your list to visit.

Such a cute atmosphere, great staff, and delicious food! I got their watermelon spritz and the french toast with beetles and whipped cream with a side of bacon and everything was delicious! Sitting outside is ideal but inside is cute too! GF and vegan options!

I highly recommend brunch at the Iron Gate Cafe; however, make certain you're on the wait list prior to arrival. Unfortunately, our experience was affected by the hostess. We waited two hours and remained first in line for well over an additional thirty minutes as those who came later were accommodated ahead of us. Nevertheless, excellent food, an exquisite ambiance in a historical home and outstanding service made it worthwhile.

I can see the manager and a regional person having a conversation. They both look at me. Continue talking. One of the women from the side bar stands up as she walks by me ask, “Is someone helping you?”. Clearly she could see no one was helping. My response, I wasn’t sure if you were taking orders or if you expect customers to know use the self ordering system.  She goes in the back to put her dirty dish in the kitchen. reviews.text:
My family walked in around 3:00PM on a Sunday. There was only 1 girl serving the entire restaurant from the bar to all tables! Although she was terribly busy, she maintained her professionalism. Especially she has kept being polite, nice, with a big smile all the time.

Food was delicious. Especially its puffy pizza.

Morgan was outstanding. She handled all the orders without fail appeared to carry out all the order seemlessly and even change the TV station to our liking. Kudos to her and her service.
Food was outstanding. We ordered pizza,  nachos and salad. Very good place to eat

6 of us enjoyed dinner here on Sunday evening before a nearby show. If you have an event in the area, this is a great option for a centrally located restaurant. And they are open Sundays, which was hard to find.
Even without a reservation, we managed to get in. However, we were there early; I suspect a table might have been harder to get later on. Service was amazing! Drink refills without asking, servers checking in just the right amount, and overall great customer service.
It is a small pub, which means it gets loud. This was fine for us, but if you are looking for a quiet spot to have long conversations, this will not be the place you want.
Pub food and pizza seems to be their specialty. Boneless wings were very good; a medium sauce had just enough spice. Mozzarella sticks also good (great marinara!) and a decent amount of them too. The pizza was delicious! I snuck a piece of my hubby's pepperoni pizza and loved it! Homemade sauce, great crust, and a nice balance of sauce to cheese. Sandwiches we ordered were good, just not outstanding. If I go back before another show, I would honestly order some more apps and pizza (I was thinking about getting chicken tenders, but didn't. Bet they are great!).
Overall, a solid choice if you are in the area for a show and looking for some great pub apps and pizza.

I go to this place once in awhile and the food is always good and drinks are too.I got the lemon pepper wings and my friend got the hot wings 🤤 I went back another night and had the buffalo chicken salad. ( big chunks of buffalo chicken) I had it with the Parmesan dressing so good 😋.

What a great menu.  It took a long time to decide on a choice because everything looks so good.

If you want fine dining and gourmet, this is probably not for you.  If you want excellent food and service, you won't be disappointed.

I only gave a 3 star on the atmosphere because it was a little too dark for my liking.

I will definitely come back for more.

reviews.text:
I visited this branch last night and had an excellent experience. It was late in the evening and there was hardly any customers.

Ordered the soup with bread, a sandwich, and pizza, and overall, I liked all the food. Will return.

The staff was courteous and I was served in a timely manner. 5/5 from me.

There is no reason this BREAD establishment makes bagels ONCE a day and it’s at night for the next day. I asked for a fresh bagel and was told those were for tmrw. So not only is it discouraging that you don’t even make the bagels the same day.. but in addition to that you make them at 6pm the night before for the next day. That’s disgusting and disappointing and there needs to be a better system for that needless to say we never receive fresh products and I will definitely not be returning. Not to mention the fact that the entire staff in the evening good around and don’t help waiting customers while your the only one in the store. If I could give no stars I would. Dont eat here my boyfriend wanted a tuna sandwhich and after waiting and waiting to be serve he changed his mind looking around the establishment and at the people just being unsanitary gross. Deff will be filing a complaint with corporate as well.

Walked in with my daughter while visiting the hospital, have never been to a Panera before, ordered a macaroni and cheese for my daughter, and they served this tiny cup, literally the size of a fancy feast cat food can, and wanted to charge $8 for it with a straight face, I'm not exaggerating at all, fold a dollar bill in half and that was about how wide the cup was, and about an inch deep... EIGHT DOLLARS FOR 2 BITES!!! I refused to pay that much for such a ridiculously small portion, canceled the remainder of the order while they were making it and walked out, never seen such a massive rip off before, it was the equivalent of paying $30 for a Big Mac.

Had a nice little lunch at the local Panera bread near the hospital during a work trip. The staff were very nice, however, the food was just alright. They did a good job making sure the spaces were being cleaned as people left, which is something that was great to see! All in all, not a bad place to sit and get some work done!
I had ordered a balsamic chicken salad with grains for lunch. Upon opening my salad I found a long, dark curly hair. The manager handled the situation and I was able to get a  refund.

reviews.text: Love getting the butter cookies from this bakery. I get the pre-boxed cookies for a quick check out. Have never been disappointed with selection inside. To be honest anything from the bakery is great. Today decided to stay for lunch at the counter after purchase on the bakery side. Bread outstanding and super fresh. Meats plentiful and tasty. Fruit smoothy good too. Service was outstanding. Waitress was also running the take out register and everything smooth and fast.

Such a cute little bakery !! I definitely got an old school Italian vibe that reminded me of Arthur Ave in NYC. I got a few donuts and they were the best I’ve ever had!! I really wish i bought more. I would make the hour & a half drive just to try it again!

Cutest little place with lots of items to choose from. I wasn't lucky to find something I liked. I got two plain cannoli's, one pistachio cannoli, a run cake and cheesecake. Only thing good was the cheesecake. The cannoli's had some small diced up fruity something, totally ruined them. But it was a cute place, I just wouldn't go back if I was in town.

The employees were smiling nonstop, and all so friendly. Ordered an 8lb cookie tray for my daughter's June wedding, and were able to enjoy lunch while there. The sandwiches were made to order and very fresh! Purchased some Italian pastries to bring home and they were wonderful. This place is a gem!
Amazing old time italian bakery. A lot of variety. Tasty pastry. String from the ceiling to wrap pastry boxes was very unique.

Whatever you do, do not come to this Dunkin’ Donuts I live nearby and will never step foot in that establishment, I have gone to this Dunkin’ Donuts a total of 5 times in the last month after 6pm , each time I went, was for a donut, there was not one pastry available each time and when I ask why that’s the case I’m given attitude,, I don’t know if they’re back there chomping on them or giving them away but this has never been the case at this Dunkin’ Donuts and it’s sad that I can’t support a local business in my neighborhood. reviews.text: This was amazing. I ordered a Cafe au lait and a slice of chocolate fudge cake. Coffee was really good for only $2.50 and that cake was something else. It made me buy another slice to-go. The ambience was great too, with paintings, warm wood-like furniture… it was awesome! I was very happy with the service. She was bubbling with happiness and was smiling the entire time while taking the order. Real positive vibes! 😁

Thanks again to the exceptional employee at PJ's Coffee Sanctuary who went out of her way today (1/2/24) to help me find a coupon on my phone that I wanted to use towards my purchase. She then  put a salad and muffin that my sister and I were sharing on two separate plates and she gave us each a hard boiled egg on our salad instead of splitting one egg between us. She didn't have to make it such a kind and heart-warming experience today but she did. The world needs more workers like her and people like her in general 🌠.

Great space to enjoy a delicious cup of coffee & relax. There’s an impressive amount of space to study or work, as well as plenty of tables for visiting with friends. I really enjoyed this spot, plus the available WiFi was perfect for my needs of sending some work emails.
Highly recommend if you’re looking for a study space with good drinks.

I’ve been coming here for 4 years now. The food is mid and the coffee is a hit or miss sometimes. But I keep coming back for the great atmosphere, it helps me focus with the dim lighting and lower music in the rooms. That being said I just ordered an iced coffee that just hit, so maybe I’ve been having bad luck before or maybe they don’t do well with hot coffees (which is what I usually go for). The baked goods are a bit lacking, but I can’t help always ordering one and being hopeful it’ll taste good.

Always the greatest coffee and baked goods.  The only problem is the staff are the most cold and attitude filled staff anywhere. If you can't be nice and enjoy your job, please find another line of work. Went in and they messed up my coffee and the Oreo cake was amazing, but fix it don't argue. Second try on coffee was excellent, why let the service ruin the experience.

reviews.text: We visited this evening (6/28/24) after dinner at The Fountain just because we've been anxious to visit local places and this appeared to be one. We learned the ice cream is made in Saratoga so we appreciated that. Unfortunately, "Karen Assistant manager" (what her name tag read) was really grumpy! She said she had been working there 30 years so maybe she is just done with customer service. It was our first time in the shop but according to other reviews I just read, this seems to be the norm for this place. Hopefully Karen can change positions, jobs or maybe have a better day!

Honestly the worst Stewart’s I’ve ever been too, which was surprising giving the location.
The cashiers were extremely rude and hostile. When we walked in, we went to the ice cream counter as we wanted ice cream. One cashier yelled “go to the other register, there’s no one at ice cream” meanwhile, she very close to the ice cream counter and could’ve easily told us she’d be with us in a sec.
We go to other register after deciding what ice cream we wanted and after we said “we’d like to get some ice cream” the cashier simply stared at us without responding. After an excessively long silence she finally says “ok what do you want”. I asked for a single scoop but to mix flavors as I always do and was told “well we don’t do that. You need to get a double scoop” but in a a nasty, rude tone. Finally we decided to go to a different Stewart’s. I asked for the SAME exact thing and didn’t have any problems. Was in and out in less than 5 mins. Do NOT go to this Stewart’s.

During our time in Albany, we stopped at many Stewart's Shops for ice cream. We always got pints at the others, but we got some scoops at this one.

My husband and I shared a Blueberry Crumble and Peanut Butter Jelly Time Waffle Cone.

I really enjoyed both flavors. If I had to pick, I'd go with PB&J. Their ice cream is a bit lighter and fluffier than most which I love.

If you're in New York, I'd definitely recommend stopping at a Stewart's to try some ice cream!

Great neighborhood watering hole. Come here often for groceries I forget to grab and coffee is always ready for the morning. Very grateful to have this location in the neighborhood. Staff is always friendly as well

I used to frequent this shop every single day as I live immediately behind it, spending on average anywhere from $20-30ish a day. I won’t be returning however.  First off let me begin with saying every employee I’ve ever interacted with up there has been nothing short of amazing to me, that is all except for one.  The young black woman that wears the headscarf was cold/rude to me repeatedly, but it finally came to a head when she pushed things too far.   I won’t tolerate being spoken to in such a nasty way nor letting her curse at me.  And I should have written this review 2 months ago when I quit going there after her outburst but figured I’d simply move on.  Well I finally write this today only after finding out that my fiance quit going there as well because the same young woman was so nasty to her as well.  I will gladly still shop at other Stewart’s when I occasionally come across them, as they’re a great chain and this doesn’t represent them as a whole.

Came here tonight for the first time. Service was quick. There were quite a good amount of customers inside.

Good was excellent. I had the same thing I had last time at the other location: soup + pizza. This time got her mango smoothie.

5/5 from me.

It's Panera you all know what to expect. You can make the same sandwich at a fraction of the cost at home but sometimes it's nice to go out . I deducted a star for the falling apart ceiling tiles lol.

This Panera Bread location is great. The establishment is clean and tidy. The customer service is great. And the food is cooked fresh and timely. I purchased a large coffee and a brioche bacon egg over easy breakfast sandwich and they were delicious.

I needed a late notice catering for a business breakfast and lunch.  I was a little out of their area but they were more than willing to help me out.  I received exceptional service and reassurance when I called and spoke with Joe regarding my dilemma.  He was professional and helpful.  I wish I could have gotten the other names of who I dealt with ( I had to call and increase my order the day of and they were able to do it! ) The delivery man was right on time for both deliveries and was very pleasant.  My first time using them for business purposes and now will be our go to place!  Food was delicious and I know I can clearly count on them for providing a great experience.

The location is clean and the atmosphere is great (like most panera's). The issue is the foood is subpar (it was free food for me) and willl always be. It's top overpriced for what you're getting (food In a bag). The chicken noodle soup is too salty and the bbq chicken salad is decent.  The sandwiches are great but they are not worth the cost of $12.75. Great staff, great atmosphere but not worth it unless your works buys it for you .

So I just want to say that I come here time to time to  with my mom who is always nice and respectful..we mainly get coffee and gas ..and on a few different occasions it seems like when ever  she asks for a fresh pot of coffee..some of the workers get an attitude and get all upset ..I'm not sure how that works but  I'm almost sure those glass coffer pots are not good no more then 15 minutes..when they have no steam coming out the coffee and u can just tell the coffee is old ..why be a miserable, rude,and sarcastic individual? For the cashier today...she honestly should try some basic customer service skills ...the way we were spoke to was completely wrong..all because we kindly and respectfully asked for fresh pot of coffee!  I'm sure when you all go out to eat u kind of expect to have a fresh,hot plate of food right!?

Day crew is typically great! Night crew not so much. Stores night crew consistently locks their doors and doesn't allow customers in well before they are said to close. Don't show up within ten minutes of their closing time you wont be served.

Staff was awesome. The fuel price gouge not so much. .34¢ cheaper on the thruway… Even before the Russia Ukraine situation they’ve been higher. There’s a truck rental just around the corner. Perfect place to gouge… absolutely disgusting considering what the Northeast has done for Stewart’s and the loyalty we show. Going to be avoiding them in general and spreading the word now. Such a shame.

If i could give no stars i would.  Finally done with stewarts a a whole, no longer referring friends , family, or customers here. They always lock the doors early.  Got here 15 min of to locked doors.  Just standing inside.  11:01 they were out the door.  Annoying how regular this is. And despite every one of their cashiers and what I would assume is their dm multiple times scanning my ID which is taped to prevent cracking (clear tape, its laminated) I was denied despite being 28 and buying from this location since it opened.  An ID is to verify identity.  How many times does it have to be verified. Also, if you've already verified the same ID at least 30 times speak up to the know nothing cashier and tell them I'm over 21. absolutely ridiculous.

I ordered a half sandwich with a fruit cup side. I paid and extra $2.69 for the fruit cup. The sandwich was great, but the fruit cup was not. It was only half full and really small. It also tasted terrible, like every musty.

They're very understaffed.  The store is poorly laid out, there's always a glut of people waiting for their food at the take out counter.  The food is ok, but not for the price.  A lot of the food is very bland. Use the app for deals and for efficiency.  The customers are always in a bad mood here as well.  Also the parking lot here is a mess and there's some obese guy with a sign that's always screaming and yelling and just being a nuisance.  Avoid.
Just had my first Panera chicken caesar salad. It was absolutely delicious. Fresh fresh crush. The lettuce was nice. The caesar dressing was excellent And not over done. I will be back!

I love this Panera! As a struggling college student this is one of my go to study spots. It is quiet, cool, and has very nice wifi. Along with this I love the workers. The service here is excellent I’ve never had a bad experience. Along with this the food is always good of course. Over all I will be coming back for sure!!!

Arrived at Halloween tine.. tru the pumpkin cream drink.. delicious. Their donuts are the best especially the peanut butter one

Great service from friendly workers! The employees know what they are doing and Shift Leader Samaria does a great job greeting customers with a friendly welcome! Would recommend to anyone around the State Capital.

Most recently, I came in back to back days asking for less ice in my drink, which they even printed on the order ticket. And for both days, I get a cup that is 75% ice. And that's the super simple issue. It's been multiple times I've asked for and paid for a large, and only received a medium.

reviews.text: You can never go wrong with au bon pain! Bon appetit !

Your hours say you are open until 3. Your lights were off and door was locked by 2:40 little ridiculous that you and all the other restaurants in the Concourse dont actually follow your open and closed times for those who may have had to push their lunches to 2:30 like I had to.

I purchased the mediterranean salad and a large chicken noodle soup. Their website boast "romaine & field greens, hummus, fresh avocado, kalamata olives, feta, grape tomatoes, red bell peppers & cucumbers". Well the avocado was NOT fresh but quite brown, the romaine and field greens were wilted and brown. They obviously don't make their salads fresh daily and fail to check and throw out days old ones. No label on the salads to let you know when the salad was prepared. The soup was definitely out of a can and not homemade. I wanted a healthy lunch but au bon pain did not live up to my expectation. If I get sick I will report you to the health department, heck I may report you anyway. I paid $10.79 for the salad and $6.29 for the large soup. I want my money back.
